org.fosstrak.reader.rprm.core
Class AntennaReadPoint

java.lang.Object
  org.fosstrak.reader.rprm.core.ReadPoint
      org.fosstrak.reader.rprm.core.AntennaReadPoint

public class AntennaReadPoint
extends ReadPoint

AntennaReadPoint extends ReadPoint. It is used to track details about the Radio Frequency characteristics and RFID statistics for the reader device.

Method Detail

create

public static AntennaReadPoint create(java.lang.String name,
                                      ReaderDevice readerDevice,
                                      org.fosstrak.hal.HardwareAbstraction reader)
                               throws ReaderProtocolException
The static method to create an instance of a AntennaReadPoint. If this method terminates successfully, the AntennaReadPoint is added to the list of read points in the reader device. If a read point with the same name exists, an exception ("ERROR_OBJECT_EXISTS") is thrown.

Parameters:
name - The name of the AntennaReadPoint
readerDevice - The reader device the source belongs to
reader - The HardwareAbstraction which contains the read point
Returns:
The instance of the created readpoint
Throws:
ReaderProtocolException - "ERROR_OBJECT_EXISTS"

getIdentificationCount

public int getIdentificationCount()
Returns the number of the successful tags that have been identified across this AntennaReadPoint. In other words, the number of tags whose unique identifier has been successfully detected by the AntennaReadPoint. Note that if a single tag's identifier is read multiple times, then the read count will increment on every successful read. It is the number of times any tag's identifier is read, not the number of unique tags which have been read.

Returns:
The count of the successful tag identifiers read at this AntennaReadPoint

getFailedIdentificationCount

public int getFailedIdentificationCount()
Returns the number of the failed tag identification attempts at the AntennaReadPoint. This count only includes failures where the tag's identifier could not be obtained, either due to a bad handle or any other reason.

Returns:
The count of the failed attempts at reading the identifier for a tag at this AntennaReadPoint

getMemReadCount

public int getMemReadCount()
Returns the number of tag memory reads at the AntennaReadPoint.

Returns:
The count of the successful tag memory reads at this AntennaReadPoint

getFailedMemReadCount

public int getFailedMemReadCount()
Returns the number of the failed tag memory reads at the AntennaReadPoint. This count only includes failures where it attempts to read tag memory but does not complete successfully.

Returns:
The count of the failed tag memory reads at this AntennaReadPoint

getFailedMemReadAlarmControl

public AlarmControl getFailedMemReadAlarmControl()
Returns the alarm control object which controls the generation of alarms triggered by failed read operations of memory banks across the AntennaReadPoint.

Returns:
An alarm control for monitoring tag memory read failures

getWriteCount

public int getWriteCount()
Returns the number of successful tag writes at the AntennaReadPoint, including writes to any of the memory banks including the tag identifier. If Write functionality is not supported by the Reader it returns 0 every time. Note that if a single tag is written multiple times, then the count will increment on every successful write. It is the number of times any tag has been written, not the number of unique tags which have been written.

Returns:
The count of the successful writes at this AntennaReadPoint

getFailedWriteCount

public int getFailedWriteCount()
Returns the number of the failed attempts to write tags at the AntennaReadPoint, including failed writes to any of the memory banks including the tag identifier. This is the number of times the reader attempted to write a tag, but the operation failed to complete successfully.

Returns:
The count of the failed writes at this AntennaReadPoint

getFailedWriteAlarmControl

public AlarmControl getFailedWriteAlarmControl()
Returns the alarm control object which controls the generation of alarms triggered by failed write operations across the AntennaReadPoint, including failed writes to any of the memory banks including the tag identifier.

Returns:
An alarm control for monitoring the number of failed writes
